postcontent:
This service is the same price for all model Glocks, Colt 1911 and Clones barrels.

This listing is for polishing of your barrel. After only 50 rounds the finish on your Glock barrel will begin to fade and look worn. It is simply a black coating that wears off. With this service you will eliminate this issue and only need to wipe off finger prints after your done at the range. Auction price is the same for all glock, XD, XDM, & 1911 barrels. I will remove all light scratches and leave it super bright. 

WILL MY BARREL RUST? NO


The Tenifer-treated slide and barrel
     Glock barrels and slides are made from quality steel which has been treated with a special "Tenifer" process.  This colorless carbo-nitrate formula enriches the steel with oxygen, sealing its pores.  Tenifer makes the steel extremely hard (as hard as industrial diamond on the Rockwell scale) and corrosion resistant.  The steel will not scratch or rust, period!  In fact, the slide is so hard you can use it to sharpen your knives.

     The barrel is treated both inside and out.  Because of this, Glock barrels do not show the normal wear associated with untreated barrels by other manufacturers.  Glock, Inc., has one barrel which has fired one million rounds and still works; another has fired 300,000 rounds and still shoots better than 1½" groups!

     Glock also parkerizes the slide and barrel to give them a matte black color.  While the parkerizing might wear off showing "bare" steel beneath, the Tenifer is still there.  In fact, it penetrates the steel to a depth of three microns.  Even a Glock which has lost all of its matte black finish is still scratch- and rust-proof.

title: For Sale:  Rare,hard to find, 100 rd. metal drum for AK47/Mak90
postcontent:
Selling a pre ban one hundred rd. metal drum mag, fits AK 47 style rifles.
    New AK47 drum still in plastic wrap with instructions sheets. Holds 100 rounds of 7.62x39 ammo. This uncommon drum holds 25 more round of ammo than the popular 75 round drum. Since the quantity of 100 round drums imported before 1994 was much less than 75 round
drums, it is geting very hard to find these drums now (it
can be confirmed by checking local shows and different
related internet boards).This could be your last chance to own of 
these highly collectable drums.Sell it a few years from now for double or triple your money, since there are no more and wont be any more imported.Sold three, have one left.Cash sale only

The drum fits the majority AK 47 variants 7.62x39 caliber currently available on the market, including (might miss a few variants) all Norinco and Polytech, Romanian WUM1 and SAR1 (except 991, which is discontinued), all Bulgarian, Hungarian (except SA-2000), MADDI, and almost all current "Preban Style" pistol grip AK variants made with US parts and foreign parks. As a rule of thumb, if the rifle can accept any 30 round double stack magzine, it can accept this drum. If the instruction says it uses a "SINGLE STACK magzine", then it is not. The Norinco AK drum is very reliable (used in the military 7.62 light machine gun a Chinese version of Russian RPK light machine gun) and convenient to load as experienced by many AK rifle and Norinco drum users/owners. It differes from and has advantages over the Russian/East German 75 round drum in 2 ways: 1) for Russian/E. German 75 round drum, one round is loaded every time from the feed lip top (need to load 75 times) just like a 30 round magzine, for the Norinco drum the back cover of the drum can be opened, 100 rd ammo can be quickly directly loaded and the cover then closed; 2) When loaded,the drum spring is under tension, as suggested by many, the spring may get weaken after loaded for extended period of time. For this  drum, it can be fully loaded withoud winding the spring. Right before use, quickly wind the drum key about 5 turns and it is ready to go. With this mechanism, the drum can be fully loaded and ready for use, but the spring tension is only applied right before use, no worry about drum spring fatigue. Function wise, the Norinco drum is superior than the Russian/E.G. drum, not to mention there is no 100 round Russian/E.G. drums (only 75 round drum). Drum is still sealed in plastic wrap in grease.
With the current climate, it is for sure NO more drums will be imported and can not be manufactured, that is why it is getting harder to have, its value appreciates fast, and be more expensive in the future.  $225 is cheap!!

Selling for $300/$400 and up on gunbroker and gunsamerica,when and if you can find one.Havent seen any at gun shows in a long time. None imported since 1994.
